        "title": "ICC Women’s T20 World Cup: England defeat South Africa by 40 runs in second semi-final in London",
        "summary": "In the ICC Women&#8217;s T20 World Cup, hosts England defeated South Africa by 40 runs in the second semi-final at the Kennington Oval in London to set up a title clash with Australia. Put in to bat first, England posted 169 for five in their 20 overs, riding on Nat Sciver-Brunt&#8217;s 75 runs off 47 […]",
        "article": "In the ICC Women&#8217;s T20 World Cup, hosts England defeated South Africa by 40 runs in the second semi-final at the Kennington Oval in London to set up a title clash with Australia. Put in to bat first, England posted 169 for five in their 20 overs, riding on Nat Sciver-Brunt&#8217;s 75 runs off 47 balls. In reply, South Africa was restricted to 129 for eight in their 20 overs. Nat Sciver-Brunt was named Player of the Match. The World Cup final will be played between England and Australia at the iconic Lord&#8217;s Cricket Ground on Sunday. Earlier, Australia booked their place in the final on Tuesday with an eight-wicket victory over the West Indies in the first semi-final in London.",
